TOC:
  A.  How to get (and contribute) to JMVC
  A.  Getting Started with JMVC


A.  How to get (and contribute) JMVC

  1.  Start a new project in git.
  
  2.  Fork ....
           http://github.com/pinhook/steal     and 
           http://github.com/pinhook/javascriptmvc
  
  3.  Add steal and javascriptmvc as submodules of your project...
           git submodule add git@github.com:_YOU_/steal.git steal
           git submodule add git@github.com:_YOU_/javascriptmvc.git jquery
           
      * Notice javascriptmvc is under the jquery folder
  
  4.  Learn a little more about submodules ...
           http://johnleach.co.uk/words/archives/2008/10/12/323/git-submodules-in-n-easy-steps
           
  5.  Make changes in steal or jmvc, and push them back to your fork.
  
  6.  Make a pull request to your fork.
  
  
A. Getting Started with JMVC

  1. Generate app: 
  			./steal/js steal/generate/app cookbook

  2. Generate scaffold:
  			./steal/js steal/generate/scaffold Cookbook.Models.Recipe

  3. Include models/controllers in cookbook/cookbook.js:
			.models('recipe')
			.controllers('recipe')

  4. Include functional tests in test/funcunit/funcunit.js:
			.then("recipe_controller_test")

  5. Open callcenter.html in a browser.

  6. Open funcunit.html in a browser (turn off popup blockers).

  7. Run tests with selenium:
  			./steal/js -selenium
  			./steal/js cookbook/test/funcunit/run.js

  8. Compress app:
  			./steal/js cookbook/scripts/compress.js

  9. Turn on production mode in callcenter.html and reload page:
			src='../steal/steal.js?steal[app]=cookbook&steal[env]=development'

  10. Generate docs:
  			./steal/js cookbook/scripts/doc.js

  10. Open cookbook/docs.html.